<p>How would one call this web service method with HTTPClient?</p>  <pre><code>PostAdminAction(string actionName, AdminInstruction adminInstruction) </code></pre>  <p>Where AdminInstruction is this:</p>  <pre><code>public class AdminInstruction {     public string actionName { get; set; }     public List&lt;Core.BaseClass.Model.KeyValue&gt; instructions { get; set; } } </code></pre>  <p>And the API call form is this:</p>  <pre><code>api/Admin?actionName={actionName}&amp;instruction={instruction} </code></pre>  <p>I have tried this:</p>  <pre><code> AdminInstruction ai = new AdminInstruction { actionName = "MyAction", instructions = new List&lt;KeyValue&gt; { new KeyValue { Key = "MyInstruction", Value = "InstrValueABC" } } };         var instr = JsonConvert.SerializeObject(ai);          var postParamsAndValues = new Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt;         {             {"actionName", "MyAction"},             {"&amp;instruction", instr}          };   using (var client = new HttpClient())         {                             var content = new FormUrlEncodedContent(postParamsAndValues);              var response = client.PostAsync("api/Admin", content);          } </code></pre>  <p>I get this error:</p>  <pre><code>System.ArgumentNullException : Value cannot be null. Parameter name: request </code></pre>  <p>From the posts I have seen here it I am following the correct methodology, unless I'm totally overlooking something - which at a late Friday night might be so.</p>